title: Grateful Dead Live at Arlington Theater on 1978-01-13
description:
Set 1

Mississippi Half Step, Mexicali Blues-> Big River, Candyman, It's All Over Now, Brown Eyed Women, Beat It On Down The Line, Friend Of The Devil, Lazy Lightning-> Supplication

Set 2

Bertha-> Good Lovin', Sunrise, Dancin' In The Streets-> Drums-> Wharf Rat-> Truckin'-> Around & Around, E: Sugar Magnolia

Pacific Alliance Benefit - "Stop Nuclear Power"

reviews.review_text: - A beautiful show in places, but not a patch on the last 2 shows.
interesting jam Dancin > drums > Jam has some interesting spacey jamming, with Jerry locked in and in an exploratory mode. See if you can catch the Close Encounters quote!

sunrise wow arlington  theater  only  seen JGB there it a small place  with a balcony  hanging third way  grate sound  this must been a barn burner   iv allways  love the song  sunrise  there some songs  that are better left alone shelfed   out of respect for the singer       i could name a few  that dead and company  are doing  in 2020      BUTT a lest there being played   / i its a year later sunrise still  sounds good 42 years later   this is raw live music before midi phil all over  his 4 string       brown eyed women  is the boys at there best
